Reasoning: The paper proposes a framework for denoising high-dimensional measurements, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The framework does not require prior knowledge of the signal or noise, which suggests it may fall under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions using the framework for matrix factorization, which is a common problem in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper applies the framework to single-cell gene expression data, which suggests it may also fall under the sub-category of computational biology (cs.SI).
